properties.description: BRING ALL OFFERS. This house was custom designed to be a picture perfect example of a Rustic Mid-Century Modern (All the Mid-Century with touches of Rustic added in). This home has a 4th non-conforming bedroom currently being used as an office. Two blocks from Cherry Creek Trail. 15 minutes to Downtown. Year-round Panoramic Mountain views. Property is perfect for entertaining with multiple outdoor seating areas. Outdoor enthusiasts have the country feel in your own private retreat in the heart of the city. Bring your RV. 40' Fenced in Concrete pad with 30 / 50 AMP service and Sewer Dump station. Smart Sprinkler System, Chicken Coop, Children's playset, Fenced backyard, Three mature flower gardens with established grape vines, blueberries, raspberries, and strawberry patch. House includes Full home audio, Radiant Floor Heating as well as a 3-Year-old HVAC unit. Internal wall insulation for extreme quiet and perfect for your home office. Solid wood doors in every room. Wired for Smart Home with Coax and CAT6 wiring in every room. Need extra warmth in the morning... Ceiling Heating units in each bath. You are ready for the storms with the 20-year hail resistant shingles put on 3 years ago. The Kitchen and Baths all have custom Granite throughout as well as hardwood cabinets with soft close, custom slide drawers, makeup table in the bathroom. In the kitchen the custom drawers continue with book shelve, spice racks, and bread box. Your breath will be taken away with the custom White Oak Barnwood Floors.

properties.description: Prepare to fall in love with this updated condo in the heart of LoHi (Lower Highlands). Equipped with vaulted ceilings, a light-filled open floorplan, city views, and blocks away from downtown and several of Denver's most popular restaurants. Condo has been updated with hardwood floors throughout (no carpet in the entire unit), and comes with one reserved underground parking space. HOA had roofs replaced less than two years ago.Enjoy your morning coffee or evening refreshments from your balcony overlooking downtown Denver. With a Walk Score of 93, there simply isn't a better location to call home in all of Denver.
